sentences: David Leslie Gilson Lavis ( GHIL-s…ôn LAY-vis, born 27 June 1951, Bedford, England) is an English drummer and portrait artist.

They both appeared (uncredited) as members of "The Nice Twelve" in the 1994 partially-improvised comedy film There's No Business... starring Raw Sex (Simon Brint and Rowland Rivron) and The Oblivion Boys.
He gained fame as the drummer with band Squeeze in the 1970s and 80s.
Lavis is currently the drummer for Jools Holland's Rhythm and Blues Orchestra, with former Squeeze bandmate Jools Holland.
Lavis now tours around the United Kingdom with Jools Holland, his long-term musical partner.
